result.execSummary:
The defendant Christopher M Osinski was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Falsely Present Noncontrolled Substance, a class I felony, Wisconsin Statutes 961.41(4)(am)1a.

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

3:12 pm  Court in session. Case Called.  Appearances given.  
DA Zeke S. Wiedenfeld appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  
Deft Christopher M Osinski in court, in custody with Atty Michael John Fitzsimmons.  
Parties have an agreement on all files.  Atty Fitzsimmons puts entire plea agreement on the court record.  
Discussion concerning restitution in files 15CM135 and 14CM283.  

16CF000180:  Deft enters GUILTY plea to Ct #1; Deft acknowledges prior conviction in support of repeater enhancer;  
16CM000490:  Deft enters GUILTY plea to Cts #1 and #2.  Deft acknowledges prior conviction in support of repeater enhancer;  
Court has plea colloquy with defendant.  Court finds deft is freely, willingly, knowingly and intelligently  waiving his rights and choosing to plead guilty.  Court adjudges defendant guilty.  
3:30 pm  Statement by Mr. Osinski.  Response by Mr. Osinski to Court's questions.  
3:31 pm  Court proceeds with making its record and sentencing the defendant.

20 days DEAD TIME CREDIT  
Judgment to be entered against the defendant and in favor of the victim for any unpaid restitution.  
Judgment is also to be entered against the defendant for any unpaid court obligations.  
  
14CM283, Ct #1:  6 months in jail, consecutive to 14CM135  
36 days DEAD TIME CREDIT  
Judgment to be entered against the defendant and in favor of the victim for any unpaid restitution.  
Judgment is also to be entered against the defendant for any unpaid court obligations.    
------------------------------------------------------------  
16CM490, Ct #1:  Total sentence of 2 years  
1 year IC and 1 year ES, consecutive to 14CM283  
16CM490, Ct #2:  Total sentence of 2 years  
1 year IC and 1 year ES, consecutive to Ct #1, 16CM490  
  
16CF280, Ct #1:  Total sentence of 2 years  
1 year IC and 1 year ES, concurrent with 16CM490, Ct #1  
  
ELIGIBLE FOR CIP AND SAP on both files.  
------------------------------------------------------------  
Conditions of extended supervision on files 14CF251, 16CM490, 16CF280:  
1)  Pay court costs and DOC supervision fees  (NOTE:  The court obligations in file 14CF251 have already been reduced to a civil judgment).  2)  Pay restitution if any is claimed.  Restitution is held open for 60 days on files 16CM490 and 16CF280.  If a restitution request is filed, deft will have 30 days to file a motion challenging restitution and request a hearing.  
3)  Counseling as recommended by Agent.  4)  No contact with the victims without the victims' and agent's consent.  5)  No weapons.  6)  No alcohol.  No drugs or drug paraphernalia.  7)  Not to operate a motor vehicle with a valid driver's license.  8)  Provide DNA sample and pay surcharge.  

Court warns defendant he cannot possess a firearm and cannot vote until his civil rights are restored.  Discussion concerning restitution owed on the CM files.  State believes that unpaid restitution on the CM files could be made a condition of ES even if he is not on ES on these files.  Defense believes that there should be a civil judgment entered against the defendant and in favor of the victims for the restitution in these files.  Court will enter a civil judgment against the defendant for his unpaid court ordered financial obligations in files 15CM135 and 14CM283.
